I’ll keep this read-only, avoid sub-agents, inspect the proposal first, then map the implied impacts across skills, commands, agents, hooks, configs, templates, and validators with line citations.
The proposal confirms 010 must land first as test substrate, 009 touches completion/agents/review prompts, 011 adds AC normalization plus validator rule and deep-review binding, with T12/T14 folding into pending 004/003 rather than new packets.
I’m narrowing from broad hits to the live integration anchors: completion gates, validator registry/rules, manifest templates, deep-review/deep-improvement command surfaces, review/context agents, hooks, and env reference flags.
Key command surfaces show both UX setup contracts and automation-owned YAML handoffs; 011 will need `/deep:start-review-loop` config/default behavior, while 010 primarily changes `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` Lane B profile/scorer handling.
The manifest templates are a shared high-risk surface: current AC text is placeholder-shaped in `spec.md.tmpl`, and `checklist.md.tmpl` has only a single “All acceptance criteria met” checkbox, matching the proposal’s warning.
Hook/config impact is mostly automation: prompt-time advisor and startup/resume hooks can surface new gate prompts or warnings, and any new AC coverage threshold needs an env reference entry because existing config docs explicitly catalog SPECKIT feature flags.
Agent impacts split by role: `@review` needs the strictest read-budget behavior, `@context` and deep-loop agents need adapted budget language, `@deep-review` needs AC/verdict binding and report schema changes, and `@orchestrate` must route/validate these updated contracts.
Runtime mirrors are also in scope: `.claude/agents/*` carries duplicate review/context/deep-loop contracts, so any prompt-contract change in `.opencode/agents/*` needs mirror alignment or an explicit mirror-exclusion decision.
The coordination items add two lower-blast changes: current-state/resume surfaces for pending 003 and constitutional/reconsolidation guidance for pending 004; they should not create new top-level packets per the proposal.
