### MISSED_SURFACES
- The proposal names key files but omits the `/deep:start-review-loop` YAML synthesis/verdict gates, which currently derive `PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` and build `review-report.md`; AC binding must land there, not only in `deep-review/SKILL.md` (`.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml:1203-1222,1282-1338`).
- It omits `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` command/YAML even though 010 is a Lane B benchmark substrate and the command fixes `lane = model-benchmark` plus profile/scorer setup (`.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md:17-18,76-99`; `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_auto.yaml:86-92`).
- It omits runtime mirrors under `.claude/agents`; review/deep-review/context contracts are duplicated there and cite their own runtime path conventions (`.claude/agents/review.md:11-14`; `.claude/agents/deep-review.md:11-18`; `.claude/agents/context.md:13-22`).
- It omits env documentation for `SPECKIT_AC_COVERAGE_FLOOR`; ENV_REFERENCE is the feature-flag table of record for SPECKIT vars (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:27-32,103-109`).
- It omits hook/advisor docs, but prompt-time advisor/startup hooks are the automation surface that should surface new routing/gate context without extra user prompts (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/config/hook_system.md:47-57`; `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md:26-40`).
- It omits manual testing/playbook updates, but 009/010/011 require regression evidence for stale verdicts, softened FAILs, reviewer oracle fixtures, and AC coverage (`.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:682-747`; `.opencode/skills/deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:525-575`).

